The Town of Watertown is a city in Middlesex County , Massachusetts , United States .
It is part of the Greater Boston area .
The population was 31,915 at the 2010 census .
Watertown is one of fourteen Massachusetts municipalities that have applied for , and been granted , city forms of government but wish to retain `` The town of '' in their official names .
Watertown is made up of six neighborhoods : Bemis , Brigham -LRB- Brigham Historic District -RRB- , Coolidge Square , East Watertown , Watertown Square and the West End .